=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"Official artwork of Belial’s Return in Diablo IV.\" data-chomp-id=\"c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"Official artwork of Belial’s Return in Diablo IV.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: Blizzard\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467\" data-recommend-id=\"image://c4dbbcf7a291d27d74eba1520ff67467\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"Official artwork of Belial’s Return in Diablo IV.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eWhether you’re running a new build, trying out a new class, or returning to \u003cem\u003eDiablo IV\u003c/em\u003e after an extended break, (a break in which you were likely playing \u003cem\u003ePath of Exile 2\u003c/em\u003e, right? I know I wasn’t alone in farming Exalted Orbs!) Whatever the case, learning how to level up fast in\u003cem\u003e Diablo IV\u003c/em\u003e should help you check out everything new this season, along with hitting endgame so that your friends don’t cruelly make fun of you! - Brandon Morgan \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/diablo-4-season-8-how-to-level-fast-endgame-50-grind-1851784331?_gl=1*10o91ha*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NzgyMCRqNjAkbDAkaDA.\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/diablo-4-season-8-how-to-level-fast-endgame-50-grind-1851784331?_gl=1*10o91ha*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NzgyMCRqNjAkbDAkaDA.\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1280\" data-height=\"720\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\" A screenshot of the Pokémon TCG Pocket: Shining Revelry trailer. The Sprigatito and Pinsir cards are visible.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\" A screenshot of the Pokémon TCG Pocket: Shining Revelry trailer. The Sprigatito and Pinsir cards are visible.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"false\" data-imagerights=\"other-license\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\" A screenshot of the Pokémon TCG Pocket: Shining Revelry trailer. The Sprigatito and Pinsir cards are visible.\" data-chomp-id=\"e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"720\" data-alt=\" A screenshot of the Pokémon TCG Pocket: Shining Revelry trailer. The Sprigatito and Pinsir cards are visible.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eImage: The Pokémon Company\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e67df23c9472ca2bce8ce724484bdf9f\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1280\" data-height=\"720\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\" A screenshot of the Pokémon TCG Pocket: Shining Revelry trailer. The Sprigatito and Pinsir cards are visible.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt’s official: ex Pokémon no longer rule unchallenged \u003cem\u003ePokémon TCG Pocket\u003c/em\u003e. While these powerful cards are still prevalent in the competitive landscape, the rise of ex-specific counters have made many of these monsters risky to bring. It’s never been more vital to find strong Pokémon that are unburdened by the ex label, but who should you use? - Timothy Monbleau \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-non-ex-pokemon-strongest-1851784250\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/pokemon-tcg-pocket-non-ex-pokemon-strongest-1851784250\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure id=\"\" data-id=\"e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A hunter in the Guild Cross Alpha Set finishes a meal alongside their Palico.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\" contenteditable=\"false\" draggable=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv contenteditable=\"false\" data-alt=\"A hunter in the Guild Cross Alpha Set finishes a meal alongside their Palico.\" data-link-reference=\"\" data-link-target=\"\" data-syndicationrights=\"true\" data-imagerights=\"fair-use\" data-hide=\"false\" data-hidecredit=\"false\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(max-width: 49.94em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_965/e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 50em) and (max-width: 63.69em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1315/e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea.jpg\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 63.75em)\" type=\"image/jpeg\" srcset=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_1600/e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea.jpg\"/\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"A hunter in the Guild Cross Alpha Set finishes a meal alongside their Palico.\" data-chomp-id=\"e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-height=\"1080\" data-alt=\"A hunter in the Guild Cross Alpha Set finishes a meal alongside their Palico.\" data-anim-src=\"\" src=\"https://i.kinja-img.com/image/upload/c_fit,q_60,w_645/e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003eScreenshot: Capcom / Samuel Moreno / Kotaku\u003c/figcaption\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cspan data-id=\"e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea\" data-recommend-id=\"image://e1281c9fef6d1d2f15a55831ff493dea\" data-format=\"jpg\" data-width=\"1920\" data-height=\"1080\" data-lightbox=\"false\" data-alt=\"A hunter in the Guild Cross Alpha Set finishes a meal alongside their Palico.\" data-recommended=\"false\" data-hide=\"false\"\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003eIt goes without saying that \u003cem\u003eMonster Hunter Wilds\u003c/em\u003e has a lot of equipment materials to keep track of. The Title 1 Update increased the amount with the likes of \u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-mh-defeat-mizutsune-bubbles-temper-1851781466\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-mh-defeat-mizutsune-bubbles-temper-1851781466\"\u003eMizutsune\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e parts and the somewhat obscurely named Pinnacle Coins. While it’s easy to know what the monster parts can be used for, the same can’t be said for a coin. Making things more complicated is that the related equipment isn’t unlocked all at once. - Samuel Moreno \u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e\u003ca data-ga=\"[[\u0026#34;Embedded Url\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;Internal link\u0026#34;,\u0026#34;https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-pinnacle-coins-location-farm-armor-1851784231?_gl=1*10o91ha*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NzgyMCRqNjAkbDAkaDA.\u0026#34;,{\u0026#34;metric25\u0026#34;:1}]]\" href=\"https://kotaku.com/monster-hunter-wilds-pinnacle-coins-location-farm-armor-1851784231?_gl=1*10o91ha*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*czE3NDk4NDQwMzkkbzY0MCRnMSR0MTc0OTg0NzgyMCRqNjAkbDAkaDA.\"\u003eRead More\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
